commit_message: require forgi version 1.1, fix #1, bump to version 1.0.8
fix bug in --baum-welch option of train_seqstructhmm (increase version to 1.07)
refactor preprocess_dataset to make it much more user-friendly
add script to recreate model graphs from model files in XML format; increase version to 1.05
fix logging bug in preprocess_dataset script
add pip dependencies for new version of forgi; increase version to v1.0.4
Remove binding sites with unknown chromosomes immediately at filtering step of preprocess_dataset
add option to skip checks at start of preprocess_dataset
preprocess_dataset: remove awk requirement and look for RNAstructure with "which"
check whether any awk variant is installed (gawk, mawk, nawk, ..)
fix genome file recommendations to hg19 (default)
preprocess_dataset: limit number of shapes predicted for one sequence to 10
improve output and error handling of bin/preprocess_dataset script
add elongation span option to preprocess_dataset script
increase version to 1.0.0; add GPL license file
improve usability: simplify output directory structure; clarify info messages on stdout and in log; clarify output file names
refactor script arguments and help messages
rename some command line parameters; updated README
check whether prerequisites are installed before preprocessing datasets
polish training and preprocessing script; add comments etc.
polish batch script; add comments etc.
Baum-Welch initialization return only best model; train_seqstructhmm supports using only best structure/shape of a sequence
ignore first character on id line in FASTA files
expand readme file: add information about executable scripts; add structure prediction tools under dependencies
